{
  "texts": [
    "Techniques to mitigate overfitting, particularly in highly heterogeneous data environments, included the introduction of regularization methods and novel loss functions designed to harmonize learning across modalities [38]- [40].",
    "Strategies for handling imbalanced data were crucial, as they directly impacted the model's ability to learn from less represented modalities effectively [31], [34], [41].",
    "Innovations in loss functions facilitated better training dynamics, especially in aligning the contributions of different modalities during the learning process [1], [2], [34], [42].",
    "However, efficiently training large-scale multimodal models continued to be a daunting task, necessitating ongoing research into more scalable and robust training methodologies [43], [44].",
    "As multimodal applications proliferate, the demand for algorithms that can effectively balance learning from varied data types has grown, emphasizing the need for continuous enhancements in training techniques [15], [42], [45]."
  ]
}